race.comment: WOLFOFFITROYSTREET (10) is a on of Ghaiyyath who has caught the eye in his recent jump-outs. Looks forward enough to make a strong debut. POETS ARTISTRY (8) was sound on debut at Avoca when third and this looks a touch easier. Has natural improvement to come and is worth following. HARRY DEVIL (1) resumes off a short break and arrives off a jump-out win at Wangaratta. Brings race experience and rates as a genuine top-three contender. DAD AND DAVE (6) debuts for the Maher yard and has shown enough in his work to suggest he can be competitive. Inside draw should see him land in a handy spot. ROCKTOBERFEST (9) is another debutant from a smart stable and his recent jump-out was encouraging. Keep very safe.
